    "summary": "Illustrates a system to count repair attempts for an item, triggering an alert if a threshold (3 or more repairs) is met, identifying it as a SCRAP candida",
    "whatItShows": "This flowchart depicts a repair counter system that tracks the number of repairs for an item. It shows a sequence of repair attempts (Reparación 1, 2, 3) and a decision point where if an item undergoes 3 or more repairs, an alert is triggered, marking it as a candidate for scrapping.",
    "whenToUse": "Use this diagram to visualize a process for identifying frequently failing items that might be more cost-effective to scrap rather than continuously repair. It's suitable for inventory management, manufacturing quality control, or asset lifecycle management systems.",
